===Anglicanism=== {{main|Anglicanism}}
====Anglican Communion==== {{main|Anglican Communion}} [[Anglicanism]] has referred to itself as the [[via media]] between Roman Catholicism and Protestantism. It considers itself to be both [[Catholic]] and [[Reformed]]. Although the use of the term "Protestant" to refer to Anglicans was once common, it is controversial today, with some rejecting the label and others accepting it.
