===Religious Society of Friends (Quakers)=== {{Main|Religious Society of Friends}} The Religious Society of Friends (Quakers), is considered historically to be a Protestant Christian denomination. It has gone through a small number of doctrinal schisms in its history as a Christian church. Today, it exists as several separate and distinct Quaker branches, and it also has an emphasis on Christian belief and practice which ranges from evangelical to liberal. {{Div col|cols=2}} *[[Friends United Meeting]] *[[Evangelical Friends International]] *[[Central Yearly Meeting of Friends]] *[[Conservative Friends]] *[[Friends General Conference]] *[[Beanite Quakerism]] *[[Britain Yearly Meeting]] *[[Ireland Yearly Meeting]] *[[New Foundation Fellowship]] {{Div col end}}
